               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-299-person2468">
                  ANN 
                  HIRONS
               <interp inst="t18320906-299-person2468" type="surname" value="HIRONS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-299-person2468" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-299-person2468" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of Alexander Hirons. On the 23rd of July I missed five sovereigns from a box up stairs; it was locked, and I found it still locked, but the key was in the room; I had not seen the money for ten days - my husband's clothes were all right in the morning - I went out at two o'clock, returned at four, and the things were gone - the prisoner, whom I had left in the house, was also gone.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-299-person2469">
                  WILLIAM 
                  ATTFIELD
               <interp inst="t18320906-299-person2469" type="surname" value="ATTFIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-299-person2469" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-299-person2469" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I apprehended the prisoner in Langston-place, Hampstead-road, on the 23rd, about nine or ten o'clock, and charged him with this robbery - he strongly denied it at first, but I found a pair of gloves, which the prosecutor claimed, and 1l. in silver; and in a box, which he said was his, I found all the property belonging to the prosecutor's son; he then said he was guilty, and that he had sold a coat at Benjamin's shop - we went, and took Benjamin that night, and found the coat and other things hanging in his shop.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-299-person2470">
                  JOHN 
                  BENJAMIN
               <interp inst="t18320906-299-person2470" type="surname" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>
