                     <interp inst="t18320906-299-person2470" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I bought the coat and things of the prisoner, between five and six o'clock that afternoon, for 28s.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner. She said, at the office, it was a 5l. note she lost - I can prove I had no money for a week before.</p>
               <p>MRS. HIRONS. I never said any thing about a 5l. note; this handkerchief was in the same box as the sovereigns.</p>
